          "body": "Verse 14 names the **pastoral aim** of God's sovereign timing: *everything God does will remain forever; there is nothing to add to it and there is nothing to take from it, for God has so worked that men should fear Him.* The unchangeable permanence of God's work is not abstract metaphysics; it is *designed to produce fear*. *Yare* — reverent awe — is the proper response to a Worker whose works cannot be improved upon. This sentence quietly anticipates the book's climax at 12:13: *Fear God and keep His commandments, for this applies to every person.* The fear of God is what Ecclesiastes 3 is *for*."
