          "title": "Dust and breath — leveling and limit",
          "body": "The chapter closes (3:18-22) by leveling man with beast in mortality. Both share the same *ruach* (breath), both die, both return to the same *aphar* (dust). Qohelet is recalling Genesis 2:7 and 3:19 — *adam* from *adamah*, dust to dust — and applying it as the great equalizer. His question in 3:21 (*who knows that the breath of man ascends upward and the breath of the beast descends to the earth?*) is **not denial of an afterlife** but acknowledgment that *under the sun* it cannot be proved. The canon will answer Qohelet's question definitively at 12:7 (*the dust will return to the earth as it was, and the spirit will return to God who gave it*) and in the NT at 2 Timothy 1:10 (Christ *abolished death and brought life and immortality to light through the gospel*). From the under-the-sun vantage, Qohelet's response is consistent: *enjoy your activities, for that is your lot* (3:22)."
